  Use Scala 3 tests that exercise `enumeratum.EnumMacros` and `enumeratum.ValueEnumMacros` through small inline wrapper methods or the normal Enumeratum-style pattern. For any `ValueEnumMacros.find*ValueEntriesImpl` coverage, configure test Scala compilation with `-Yretain-trees`; the macro source explicitly aborts without it and the README documents this Scala 3 limitation. Keep values literal so the macro can inspect them at compile time.
  
